    "Although strict accuracy was low across all models, close-enough accuracy remained between 53-61%, with Claude again achieving the highest consistency (88%).",
    "Overall, Claude 3.5 demonstrates strong and stable phishing detection capabilities, consistently achieving around 66-67% strict accuracy",
    "This study has several limitations that must be acknowledged.",
    "First, the dataset is constrained by the limited sources from which the emails were collected.",
    "Many existing public phishing and spam datasets are outdated and often lack critical fields such as embedded URLs, file attachments, or sender information."
